{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-0005-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Attachments",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1738454400000,
  "modified": 1775756670528,
  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Every item has an "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "attachments"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " array that establishes composition relationships. Attachments represent \"other items that are relevant to this item\". The nature of the relevance is not specified: the spatial view chooses to interpret attachments as child windows; other views will have their own interpretation."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Attachments Array Structure"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Attachments are objects with an "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "id"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " and a "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "view"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " configuration:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "attachments: [\n  {\n    id: \"attachment-item-uuid\",\n    view: {\n      type: \"view-uuid\",  // Required: which view renders this attachment\n      // ... view-specific configuration\n    },\n    previousView: { ... }  // Optional: for view toggling\n  }\n]"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "The "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "view"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Object"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "view"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " object specifies how this parent displays this child:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":table",
        [
          ":thead",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Property"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Purpose"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":tbody",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "type"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":strong",
                {
                  "s": "Required."
                }
              ],
              {
                "s": " UUID of the view to use"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "(others)"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "View-specific configuration"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Spatial Container Views"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "For "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "ef793c27-2d4b-4c99-b05a-2769db5bc5a9"
          },
          {
            "s": "spatial-canvas-view"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", the view object includes positioning:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "view: {\n  type: \"spatial-canvas-view-uuid\",\n  x: 100,\n  y: 50,\n  width: 400,\n  height: 300,\n  z: 1,\n  minimized: false,\n  maximized: false,\n  pinned: false\n}"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "List Views"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "For list views, the view object might just have "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "type"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ":"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "view: { type: \"compact-view-uuid\" }"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Managing Attachments"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The API provides attachment management functions:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "// Add an attachment\nawait api.attach(parentId, attachmentId, viewConfig?);\n\n// Remove an attachmen\nawait api.detach(parentId, attachmentId);\n\n// Update child's view configuration\nawait api.updateViewConfig(parentId, attachmentId, { x: 200, y: 100 });\n\n// Change which view renders an attachment\nawait api.setAttachmentView(parentId, attachmentId, newViewId);"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "View Toggling with "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "previousView"
          }
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "When switching an attachment's view, the old configuration is preserved:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "// Before toggle\n{\n  id: \"item-1\",\n  view: { type: \"expanded-view\", ... },\n  previousView: null\n}\n\n// After toggle to compact view\n{\n  id: \"item-1\",\n  view: { type: \"compact-view\" },\n  previousView: { type: \"expanded-view\", ... }  // Preserved!\n}\n\n// Toggle back restores expanded-view with its configuration"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Contextual vs Preferred Views"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Attachments can be displayed differently in different parents:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Contextual view"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " (in parent's "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "view.type"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": "): \"How this parent shows this attachment\""
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Preferred view"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " (on item itself): \"How this item prefers to be shown\""
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Contextual overrides preferred. See "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "aaaaaaaa-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "kernel:view"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " for the full resolution hierarchy."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Ordering"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "attachments"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " array is "
        },
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "ordered"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". Array position determines:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Display order in lists"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Z-index base in spatial layouts (higher index = rendered later = on top by default)"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Cycle Prevention"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "api.attach()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " checks for cycles:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "A cannot be an attachment of itself"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "A cannot be an attachment of B if B is already a descendant of A"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "This prevents infinite rendering loops."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Cascade Deletion"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "When an item is deleted:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ol",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "It's removed from all parents' "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "attachments"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " arrays"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "The item itself is deleted from storage"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Its own attachments are "
            },
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "not"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " deleted (they become orphans)"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Orphan items still exist but aren't reachable through navigation. Use search to find them."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Design Rationale"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Why No Special Container Type?"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "There is no special \"container\" concept in the kernel. A container is simply an item whose view happens to render attachments. This means:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Any item can contain other items"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Container behavior is a view concern, not a data model concern"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Hierarchical composition emerges from simple rules"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Why Graph Structure (Not Tree)?"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Items can appear in multiple containers simultaneously. A note can be in both \"Project X\" and \"Meeting Notes.\" This requires a DAG (directed acyclic graph) rather than a strict tree. Cycle prevention ensures rendering terminates."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Why Position Data in Attachments?"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Position data could live in a separate layout table, but embedding it in the attachment reference avoids synchronization issues (child removed but layout entry remains). Single source of truth."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "See Also"
        }
      ],
      [
